// Regression guard for the !=/`!`-followed-by-var disambiguation.
// `x != y` MUST parse as a neq binary expression, not as a
// send_method with method name starting with `=`. The grammar
// distinguishes by what follows the `!`: a var (method name) means
// send_method; anything else (including `=`, `(`, `?`) means an
// operator or plain send.
new x, y in {
  if (x != y) { @0!(1) }
}
